````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
Can you give us a few details about yourself, where you were born,
attended schools, career etc:-
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
Hello Felice, I'll do my best to answer your questions as
truthfully (haha) as I can. :-)

I've lived all my 24 years in a small town called "Sater" in
the middle of Sweden.

School however have never been something I have liked, so 
after the 9 first years (which ended up with quite lousy
grades) I choosed an easy Highschool education.

After school I have worked as almost anyting you can think
of. The job situation in Sweden -sucks- at the moment and
all jobs I've had so far have been either temporay or quite
low paid. So I don't have any career to brag about either,
sad case, ehh?

The future is looking somewhat brighter though. :-) 


````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
How did you start off in the world of hobbyist computing ?
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
Hmm, tricky question. But I guess it was back in the days
of Speccy vs C64 wars. And I decided to get an MSX instead. :)
€Main reason of getting the first compy was ofcourse the games.

And to be perfectly honest, I still enjoy the old MSX games better
than todays Jaguar or Falcon ones.


```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
What prompted you to set up the Dead Hackers Society ?
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
Once upon a time (approx 6 years ago now) me and a few
friends decided to get a place where we could all put our
computers into one place, rather than each one of us were
working at separate places with our projects.

So one day we did get our own place (in a cement-room
down in a cellar), and we naturally called it "The Bunker".
After a while down in that cement-box we started to talk about
joining a few democrews together which already in practise was
one team. So we did, and called it the "Dead Hackers Society".


