`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
Which are your favourite demos on the ST, STE and Falcon ?
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
I like alot of them, many for different reasons, so I could
never tell just "that" demo is my favourite.. But among
the ones I really adore are:

Brain Damage (STe), Steps (ST, probably my favourite music-
demo ever), Synergy Megademo (ST), Obnoxious (Falcon), 
Autowashen.. (Falcon).

Alot of people will probably yell something like "noo what about
Sono, Eko System.. blabla". Well these ones might be better,
but the first feeling I get from a demo is usually what I
will always think of it. And when I first saw BD, Steps and the
others I was really really happy about them.

€
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
What are your favourite games of all time, on any system ?
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
I liked so many games back in the mid 80's, and dislike so
many games today so my favourites still are Galaga (MSX),
Knightmare (MSX), Wings of Death (ST) and a few others.
Note that I am no fan of strategy games that takes weeks
to play. I just can't justify the time it takes to play these,
but sure, I guess they are really good as well.


`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
What prompted you to start in comms and why do you call a BBS ?
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````
I bought my first modem not so long ago ('90 I beleive) and back then
the main reason was to download the new demos from BBS (like Lynx BBS,
Red Dwarf, Eagles Nest among others). But quite soon the main goal
of calling them was to discuss matters with the other users in
the mail areas. These were the really golden years of my bbs calling.

Unfortunately, since I started to use internet my interest for the 
bbs'sgot weaker and weaker. And now, I never call them anymore. 
Call it betrayal, lameness, boring or whatever you like, but it's just
how things went out.  


